01/12/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The country celebrates National Unification Day on Monday (1 December) with a series of public and cultural events. 
President Ion Iliescu held a reception on Saturday, inviting diplomats and local politicians to observe 85 years of unity. 
Iliescu stressed that December 1, 1918 marked the beginning of institutional modernisation, democratisation and economic and social development. 
(Rompres - 01/12/03; Rompres - 29/11/03)
